<p align="center"><font size="7">Starting the Virtual Classroom Image Server</font></p>

<p align="center">&nbsp;</p>

<p align="left"><font size="6">In order to share your personal emoticons with 
other people in the classroom, you must connect be able to connect to a known 
Image Server.&nbsp; This tutorial will show you how to set up the image server 
on your local host should one not exist.</font></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">1. Using the command line utility, browse to the 
location of the Image Server on your hard drive.</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_35.jpg" width="669" height="254"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">2. Start the Image Server as follows:</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_36.jpg" width="669" height="254"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">3. Configure the port number you wish the server 
to run on (default is 7654) and then click the start button:</font></p>
<p align="left"><img border="0" src="page_33.jpg" width="408" height="134"></p>
<p align="left">&nbsp;</p>
<p align="left"><font size="6">4. The image server is now up and running.</font></p>

